er offering:** ___ shares.\n    *   **Voting Power:** Class A will hold ___% (or ___% if option exercised) and Class B will hold ___% (or ___% if option exercised) of the voting power after the offering.\n*   **Beneficial Ownership Assumptions:** Pre-offering ownership is based on 6,932,508,000 shares of Class A and 5,602,790,410 shares of Class B outstanding as of May 1, 2026. Post-offering ownership is based on ___ shares of Class A and ___ shares of Class B outstanding as of May 1, 2026.\n*   **Exclusions from Post-Offering Share Count:** The share counts do not reflect:\n    *   Shares issuable upon exercise of the underwriters’ option.\n    *   Shares issuable upon exercise of outstanding stock options granted under the Equity Plans as of March 31, 2026 (weighted-average exercise price of $___).\n    *   Shares issuable upon exercise of stock options granted under the Equity Plans after March 31, 2026.\n    *   Shares that may be purchased through the directed share program.\n\n### 3. 2026 Stock Split Adjustments\n*   **The Split:** On May 4, 2026, SpaceX effected a five-for-one (5-for-1) forward stock split of its authorized, issued, and outstanding shares of Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock (the "2026 Stock Split"). \n*   **Retroactive Adjustment:** All share and per-share information included in the prospectus has been retroactively adjusted to reflect the 2026 Stock Split for all periods presented. The consolidated financial statements were also retrospectively recast to include this split.\n*   **Preferred Stock Conversion Rate:** The conversion rate of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was proportionately adjusted to factor in the 2026 Stock Split.\n*   **Beneficial Ownership Table:** The pre- and post-offering percentage ownership information explicitly gives effect to the 2026 Stock Split (along with the Class C Reclassification and Preferred Conversion).\n\n### 4. Capitalization Assumptions (Class C Reclassification & Preferred Conversion)\nUnless otherwise indicated, all information in the prospectus assumes or gives effect to:\n*   **Class C Reclassification:** The reclassification of all outstanding Class C common stock into an aggregate of ___ shares of Class A common stock prior to the offering.\n*   **Preferred Conversion:** The conversion of all outstanding preferred stock into an aggregate of ___ shares of Class A common stock and ___ shares of Class B common stock.\n*   **Charter Effectiveness:** The effectiveness of the company\'s charter and bylaws upon completion of the offering.\n*   **No Insider Purchases:** No purchase of shares in this offering by directors, officers, or existing investors.\n*   **No Underwriter Option:** That underwriters do not exercise their option to purchase additional shares.\n\n### 5. Other Per-Share and Share Count Disclosures\n*   **Dilution Sensitivity:** \n    *   If the IPO price increases/decreases by $1.00 per share, the dilution in pro forma net tangible book value per share to new investors would equal $___ or $___, respectively.\n    *   If the number of shares offered increases/decreases by ___ shares, the dilution would be $___ or $___, respectively.\n    *   Each $1.00 change in the IPO price changes total consideration paid by new investors and all shareholders by $___ million.\n*   **Use of Proceeds Sensitivity:** Each $1.00 change in the assumed IPO price changes net proceeds by approximately $___ million. An increase/decrease of one million shares offered changes net proceeds by $___ million.\n*   **Pending Transactions Excluded from Share Counts:**\n    *   **EchoStar Spectrum Transaction:** Excludes the payment of ___ shares of Class A common stock and cash consideration for the $19.6 billion acquisition of EchoStar spectrum. This consists of approximately $11.1 billion in equity (~52.4 million shares at a fixed value of $212/share) and up to $8.5 billion in debt payoff. *Note: These amounts do not give effect to the 2026 Stock Split