SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock were only permitted to convert to **Class A** SpaceX Common Stock."\n\n---\n\n## 2. Class C Reclassification\n\n- **Definition:** "the reclassification of all of the outstanding shares of our Class C common stock into an aggregate of [blank] shares of Class A common stock (the \'Class C Reclassification\')"\n- **Pro forma assumption (capitalization table):** "the Class C Reclassification as if such reclassification had occurred on **March 31, 2026**"\n- **Pro forma assumption (EPS):** "the Class C Reclassification as if such reclassification had occurred as of **January 1, 2025**"\n- **Beneficial ownership table:** "after giving effect to the Class C Reclassification, the Preferred Conversion, and the 2026 Stock Split"\n- **Dilution section:** "the Class C Reclassification and the Preferred Conversion as if such reclassification and conversion occurred on March 31, 2026"\n\n---\n\n## 3. Preferred Conversion (SpaceX)\n\n- **Definition:** "the conversion of the outstanding shares of all our preferred stock into an aggregate of [blank] shares of our Class A common stock and [blank] shares of our Class B common stock (the \'Preferred Conversion\')"\n- **Pro forma assumption (capitalization table):** "the Preferred Conversion as if such conversion had occurred on **March 31, 2026**"\n- **Pro forma assumption (EPS):** "the Preferred Conversion as if the conversion occurred on **January 1, 2025**"\n- **EPS adjustment:** "Pro forma adjustment to reflect the Preferred Conversion as if the conversion occurred on January 1, 2025, basic and diluted"\n- **Deemed dividend reversal:** "Pro forma adjustment to reverse the deemed dividend on SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, basic and diluted"\n\n---\n\n## 4. Capital Structure Changes Affected by the 2026 Stock Split\n\n### The Split Itself\n- "On **May 4, 2026**, the Company effected a **five-for-one forward stock split** of its authorized, issued, and outstanding shares of Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock (\'2026 Stock Split\')."\n- "In May 2026, the Board approved the 2026 Stock Split, pursuant to which each share of the Class A, Class B, and Class C SpaceX Common Stock issued and outstanding was split into **five shares** of the same class of SpaceX Common Stock."\n- Note: Class D common stock was **not** subject to the 2026 Stock Split.\n\n### Retroactive Adjustment\n- "All share and per share information has been **retroactively adjusted** to reflect the 2026 Stock Split for all periods presented."\n- "Unless otherwise stated or the context otherwise requires, all share and per share information included in this prospectus have been retroactively adjusted to reflect the 2026 Stock Split."\n\n### Preferred Stock Conversion Rate Adjustment\n- "The conversion rate of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was **proportionately adjusted** to factor in the 2026 Stock Split."\n\n### xAI Preferred Conversion (Pre-Split Basis)\n- All xAI preferred stock conversion ratios (0.1433 shares per preferred share) are explicitly stated as being "**on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis**," meaning the effective post-split ratio would be approximately 0.7165 shares (0.1433 × 5).\n\n### xAI Preferred Stock Accounting Treatment\n- "Because the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was legally outstanding during all historical periods prior to the xAI Merger and represented a separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity, the conversion of xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock into SpaceX Common Stock is recognized **only as of the closing of the xAI Merger, and not retrospectively**."\n- "The historical consolidated balance sheets and consolidated statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and shareholders\' equity reflect the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock as outstanding xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock consistent with its legal form and rights during those periods and are **not recast on an as-converted basis** for all periods presented prior to the xAI Merger Date."\n\n### X Merger Exchange Ratios (Retroactively Recast)\n- "Upon the effective date of the X Merger, each class of common stock of X Holdings Corp. (\'X Common Stock\') was converted to **2.776 shares** of xAI Common Stock of the same class (rounded down to the nearest whole share)."\n- "each class of common stock of X.AI Corp. (\'xAI Corp. Common Stock\') was converted to **1.000 share** of xAI Common Stock of the same class."\n- "As a result of the Mergers, all of X, X.AI Corp. and xAI Common Stock are being presented in the historical financial statements **as if they had been converted into SpaceX Common Stock at the applicable exchange rate for all periods presented**."\n\n### 2022 Stock Split (Prior Split)\n- "In 2022, the Board approved a stock split (the \'2022 Stock Split\'), pursuant to which each share of the SpaceX Common Stock issued and outstanding was split into **ten shares** of SpaceX Common Stock."\n\n---\n\n## 5. Historical/Pre-Split Transaction Prices\n\n### xAI Series A Cash Election Price\n- "For xAI Series A Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, all holders that were an eligible service provider could elect to receive cash of **$75.46 per share** of xAI Series A Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock **(on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis)**."\n- This $75.46 figure is the only explicit historical per-share transaction price disclosed, and it is expressly flagged as pre-split. On a post-2026 Stock Split basis, this would equate to approximately $15.09 per share ($75.46 ÷ 5).\n\n### Qualified IPO Threshold (SpaceX Preferred Auto-Conversion Trigger)\n- "The SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock automatically converts upon the earlier of (i) the Company\'s sale of its common stock in a public offering pursuant to a registration statement under the Securities Act of 1933, in which the **pre-public offering market capitalization** of the Company is at least **$6.0 billion** and which results in aggregate cash proceeds to the Company of not less than **$250 million** (\'Qualified IPO\')."\n\n### IPO Offering Price (Current, Not Historical)\n- "an initial public offering price of $[blank] per share of Class A common stock (the midpoint of the price range set forth on the cover of this prospectus)" — this is a forward-looking offering price, not a historical pre-split price.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Pre-Split References\n\n| Item | Pre-Split Value/Rate | Post-Split Equivalent (÷5) |\n|------|---------------------|---------------------------|\n| xAI preferred → SpaceX Class A conversion ratio | 0.1433 shares | ~0.7165 shares |\n| xAI preferred → SpaceX Class B conversion ratio | 0.1433 shares | ~0.7165 shares |\n| xAI Series A cash election price | $75.46/share | ~$15.09/share |\n| SpaceX preferred conversion rate | 10 shares (implied pre-split) | 50 shares (stated post-split) |',
